You are building a Blazor Web App for building inspectors on construction sites. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-24449df1f76747f58c49143ba5f97409/SiteInspector/` with Interactive WebAssembly global mode.

The project structure:
- `SiteInspector/` - server project with `Components/App.razor`, `Program.cs`
- `SiteInspector.Client/` - WebAssembly client project with `Pages/`, `Layout/`, `Program.cs`

Requirements:
- Inspectors fill out safety checklists and add notes at each site visit
- Photos are attached to inspection reports
- Must work OFFLINE (PWA with service worker + IndexedDB for local storage)
- When connectivity returns, data syncs back to the server
- Mobile-first (phones/tablets) — large tap targets, responsive
- Low-latency UI — inspectors tap through checklist items quickly
- No authentication

